Three suspects allegedly involved in a series of armed robberies were arrested during an operation by the Crime Intelligence Unit and Detectives Unit in Tzaneen yesterday (Thursday) and are expected to appear in the Lenyenye Magistrate s Court today (Friday) or on Monday. Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said the men were arrested in Balloon village in Maake and aged 20, 25 and 30. A firearm with three cartridges was recovered. Meanwhile a Seshego Cluster Task Team and Crime Intelligence Unit arrested a 35-year-old suspect on charges of possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition yesterday (Thursday). Two firearms and nine live rounds of ammunition were recovered. The confiscated items were hidden in a music system, Ngoepe said. The suspect will appear in the Seshego Magistrate s Court soon. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com Featured photo: A firearm and ammunition hidden in a music system were confiscated and one suspect arrested during an operation in Seshego yesterday (Thursday). (photo supplied) &nbsp;